      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:30:5",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قَضَى أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) فِيمَا كَانَ مِنْ جِرَاحَاتِ الْجَسَدِ أَنَّ فِيهَا الْقِصَاصَ أَوْ يَقْبَلَ الْمَجْرُوحُ دِيَةَ الْجِرَاحَةِ فَيُعْطَاهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Mahboub, from Is’haq Bin Ammar, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> judged with regards to what was from the injuries of the body, that regarding these is the retaliation, or the injured one can accept the wergild for the injuries, so he should be given it’."
        ]
      }
    }
